2026-05-14 | Find All Occurrences of Subarray

	Question
Return all starting indices where b occurs in a.
	Approach
1.	Traverse every possible starting index in a  
2.	For each index i:
		check whether:
				a[i+j] == b[j]
		for all j  
3.	If all elements match:
		store i  
	Time Complexity
	O((n-m+1) × m)
	Space Complexity
	O(1) extra
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> findSubarray(vector<int>& a, vector<int>& b) {
        int n = a.size();
        int m = b.size();
        vector<int> ans;
        for(int i = 0; i <= n - m; i++){
            bool match = true;
            for(int j = 0; j < m; j++){
                if(a[i + j] != b[j]){
                    match = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if(match)
                ans.push_back(i);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
This is essentially:
		pattern matching on arrays  
We simply compare every valid window of size m
with array b.
